entries.femaleVariant: Look, you gotta try that moonshine of mine. Triple-filtered. Taste of freedom, choom.
Ever think about branching out, selling it to some club in town?
Nah. All for me. Don't drink anything else now, not even water. Like a mouthful of rusty metal, blech!
'Cause whatever's coming out of the tap isn't water. They use the real stuff to water down the fuel, then make us drink whatever swill's left.
Whole reason I put a container up on the roof, started collecting rainwater. Tastes a little like gasoline, sure, but that's ok. Takes me back to when I was a kid.
You guys had a gas car?
Nah, come on. Used to go to town to siphon. You pull out the fuel cap, then get it started sucking on a tube. Made some extra eds that way.
